  "instructions": [
    "Prepare the vine leaves by rinsing them thoroughly.",
    "Heat a pot with coconut milk, thyme, garlic, onion, ginger, and fish sauce (if using). Simmer for about 10 minutes until flavors meld together.",
    "Add tomato puree and basil, continue simmering for an additional 5-7 minutes. The mixture should be thickened slightly but not soupy.",
    "Slowly stir in heavy cream while continuously stirring to prevent burning. Season with salt and pepper as needed.",
    "Serve the dish hot over cooked rice or as a side dish. Garnish with fresh herbs like cilantro if desired."
